All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Admin
The Admin class is responsible for managing administrative operations, including user login, client management, program tracking, instructor management, and article approval/rejection.
Article
Represents an article that can be submitted by an instructor.
ArticleType
Enum representing the different types of articles that can be submitted.
Client
Represents a client in the system, with functionality to manage programs, goals, feedback, dietary preferences, and subscription plans.
Database
The Database class serves as a mock database for storing various entities such as clients, instructors, articles, programs, feedback, and plans.
DatabaseService
The DatabaseService class serves as a middle layer to let other classes interact with the real Database DatabaseService is the only class with direct access to Database class
Feedback
The Feedback class represents feedback submitted by clients.
Instructor
The Instructor class represents an instructor within the system.
Main
 
Message
The Message class represents a message sent by an instructor to a client.
Plan
The Plan class represents a subscription plan for clients or instructors.
PlanClient
The PlanClient class extends the Plan class and represents a subscription plan for clients.
PlanInstructor
The PlanInstructor class extends the Plan class and represents a subscription plan for instructors.
Program
The Program class represents a training program offered by an instructor.
Progress
Represents a client's progress towards a specific fitness goal.
